          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Congressional Personal Safety Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to allow a Member of Congress who is carrying a valid Member identification document and who is not otherwise prohibited from transporting, shipping, or receiving a firearm to carry a firearm for any lawful purpose: (1) in any state; and (2) in the Capitol Buildings, other than the U.S. Capitol, and on the Capitol Grounds.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-06-20T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
